I am a seasoned mage, and rarely have problems with pets, even in bad pathing situations.  Even so, Mages often get bashed the first time there is a problem caused by a pet (oddly, chanters are allowed to make tons of mistakes, as are tanks, etc.).<br>
<br>
That being said, raid leaders who don't fully understand a class and then limit what that class can do, usually do so out of ignorance, and I sure don't want to follow them into any situation.<br>
<br>
Mages also get a great raid pet, Rage of Zomm, that costs 200 mana, quads in the upper 70s, is huge, and is target based.  So pathing issues are gone.  If a raid leader won't let you use this pet, they are truly ignorant.  Zero risk, since if it's feared, or you call it off, or whatever, it will die.  It also has almost no HP so it will die after it gets hit a few times should it end up aggroing.  Only useful on raids and fear-kiting.<br>
<br>
